responses.text:
Go, go, my naughty girl, and kiss
the trembling stars above the lane;
let midnight grant you dreams of bliss,
as moonlight weaves through windowpane.
Slip softly past the garden gate,
your laughter trailing in the mist;
let wonder dance with hands of fate,
and lips remember all you’ve wished.
For every secret night has kept,
for every hope you dare to twirl—
go claim the magic while you’ve wept,
go, go, my daring, naughty girl.

Go, go, my naughty girl, and kiss
the laughter hidden in the rain;
dance reckless where the puddles hiss—
your shadow flung beyond the lane.
Let every petal, every thorn,
be startled by your fearless song;
let wild winds carry, newly born,
the mischief you have held so long.
Tonight, the world is yours to dare—
to steal a moment, break the mold;
go, kiss the darkness if you care,
and paint the twilight bright and bold.
